font-size:12pt">It is not easy to run a children’s home. We deal with children whose behaviour can be very challenging. Most are non-verbal so cannot ea</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">sily communicate their needs, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">worries or concerns. Our staff are dedicated and have to</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> work most weekends and many bank holidays. Our staff do not earn a lot of money although we gave them all a pay rise last year even though we did not receive any additional fees for this. We are under constant financial pressure from </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">local</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">authorities</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> to </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">cut fees but we cannot compromise on the standards of care</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="16" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The comments </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">we make </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">a</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">re in respect of </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">our</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">own </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">large home located in the South East of England which provides residential accommodation for children and young people with learning disabilities.  There 